Starr and Lendon, CNN The US military is sending a double-barreled message this week to potential adversaries in the Pacific. A US Navy submarine carrying nuclear-tipped ballistic missiles is visiting Guam for the first time since the late 1980s and US and Japanese troops will practice amphibious landings on Pacific islands. The submarine USS Pennsylvania (SSBN 735) is making what the Navy formally calls a "scheduled port visit" to the US territory in the Pacific, according to a Navy press statement But a US defense official says that both Japanese and South Korean delegations are in Guam at this time and will be offered rare tours of the submarine. The visit comes as military tensions are high both with North Korea over its nuclear program, and China, over its moves in the South China Sea. The Navy is making the public statement about the Pennsylvania in part to show its presence to allies and adversaries in the region. "This specific visit to Guam reflects the United States' commitment to its allies in the Indo-Asia-Pacific, and complements the many exercises, training, operations, and other military cooperation activities conducted between the US and its partner nations," the Navy said in its statement. "Ballistic missile submarines such as USS Pennsylvania are on patrol continuously, providing a critical, stabilizing and highly effective element of the US nuclear deterrence force." The Pennsylvania, one of 14 Ohio-class ballistic missile submarines in the US fleet, carries 24 Trident II D-5 ballistic missiles, according to the US Navy. Each missile carries multiple warheads which can be programmed to hit different targets (para. 1-9).

The likeliest date for the reunions is around the Chuseok public holiday, which is celebrated both in the north and south. The Chuseok for 2016 has already past and the next one will be held on October 4, 2017. As relations between the two nations and the U.S. have tightened since 2015 due to the North Korean nuclear programme, a new reunion looks unlikely anytime soon. The beginning of the year is always a time of heightened tension due to the annual ROK-U.S. military exercise. There is political will for the reunions in the South due to the fact that many of the separated family members are of high age, hence they should be allowed to meet before their death.

Kim III will not allow family reunion meeting at all for at least a year. Demand for final peace treaty negotiations will not be accepted and he has no incentive for such visits. Further, such visits are contrary to US ( and ROK) goal of complete isolation of DPRK to render sanctions effective. Futher, do not see President Park allowing such ROK visits when DPRK is nuclear testing and continuing ballistic tests. Finally Park cannot allow visits when any ROK citizens could be held hostage. Kim III cannot allow such visits, it would allow defections.
